#+TITLE The Dezyne server, services, client.

Dezyne is built and deployed using [[https://gnu.org/s/guix][Guix]].

* Setup Guix

** On Ubuntu

   As root (sudo -i) do
   #+BEGIN_SRC bash
   wget -O setup-guix.sh 'http://git.oban.verum.com/?p=buildmaster/development.git;a=blob_plain;f=release/setup-guix.sh;hb=refs/heads/master'
   wget -O setup-guix-user.sh 'http://git.oban.verum.com/?p=buildmaster/development.git;a=blob_plain;f=release/setup-guix-user.sh;hb=refs/heads/master'
   wget -O setup-guix-offload-user.sh 'http://git.oban.verum.com/?p=buildmaster/development.git;a=blob_plain;f=release/setup-guix-offload.sh;hb=refs/heads/master'
   wget -O setup-postgres.sh 'http://git.oban.verum.com/?p=buildmaster/development.git;a=blob_plain;f=release/setup-postgres.sh;hb=refs/heads/master'
   wget -O setup-shepherd.sh 'http://git.oban.verum.com/?p=buildmaster/development.git;a=blob_plain;f=release/setup-shepherd.sh;hb=refs/heads/master'
   chmod +x setup-guix.sh setup-guix-user.sh setup-guix-offload.sh setup-postgres.sh setup-shepherd.sh
   ./setup-guix.sh
   #+END_SRC

   As user do
   #+BEGIN_SRC bash
   wget -O setup-guix-user.sh 'http://git.oban.verum.com/?p=buildmaster/development.git;a=blob_plain;f=release/setup-guix-user.sh;hb=refs/heads/master'
   chmod +x setup-guix-user.sh
   ./setup-guix-user.sh
   #+END_SRC

** Or install [[https://gnu.org/s/guix][GuixSD]]

* Get it

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  mkdir -p src
  cd src && git clone git.oban.verum.com:~buildmaster/development.git
  #+END_SRC

* Build it

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  guix environment -l guix.scm
  ./configure
  make
  #+END_SRC

** Run uninstalled programs

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
   ./pre-inst-env gdzn ...
  ./pre-inst-env dzn ...
  #+END_SRC

** Run regression test

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  guix environment dezyne-regression-test
  ./pre-inst-env test test/hello/helloworld

  ./pre-inst-env test test/regression
  #+END_SRC

*** Run regression through node dzn client, daemon and server

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  guix environment dezyne-regression-test
  DZN=dzn ./pre-inst-env test test/hello/helloworld
  #+END_SRC

* Create a persistent build environment

** in your default profile

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  guix package -m release/manifest.scm
  #+END_SRC

** or in a special named profile

  #+BEGIN_SRC bash
  guix package -p ~/.config/guix/verum -m release/manifest.scm
  #+END_SRC

